Applying Colors and Backgrounds in CSS
CSS offers various ways to apply colors and backgrounds to HTML elements.

Colors
Hex Code: A six-digit hexadecimal code representing the amounts of red, green, and blue in the color.
Example: #FF0000 (red)
RGB: Represents the color using red, green, and blue values, each ranging from 0 to 255.
Example: rgb(255, 0, 0) (red)
HSL: Represents the color using hue, saturation, and lightness.
Example: hsl(0, 100%, 50%) (red)
Backgrounds
Solid Color: Sets a uniform background color.
Example: background-color: #FF0000;
Gradient: Creates a smooth transition between multiple colors.
Example: background: linear-gradient(to right, #FF0000, #00FF00);
Image: Sets an image as the background.
Example: background-image: url('image.jpg');
Example HTML and CSS
HTML
<!DOCTYPE html>
<html>
<head>
    <title>Colors and Backgrounds Example</title>
    <style>
        .hex-color {
            background-color: #FF0000;
        }

        .rgb-color {
            background-color: rgb(0, 255, 0);
        }

        .hsl-color {
            background-color: hsl(120, 100%, 50%);
        }

        .gradient-background {
            background: linear-gradient(to right, #FF0000, #00FF00);
        }

        .image-background {
            background-image: url('image.jpg');
            background-size: cover;
        }
    </style>
</head>
<body>
    <div class="hex-color">Hex Color</div>
    <div class="rgb-color">RGB Color</div>
    <div class="hsl-color">HSL Color</div>
    <div class="gradient-background">Gradient Background</div>
    <div class="image-background">Image Background</div>
</body>
</html>

Explanation:

Hex Color: The hex-color div has a red background using a hex code.
RGB Color: The rgb-color div has a green background using RGB values.
HSL Color: The hsl-color div has a cyan background using HSL values.
Gradient Background: The gradient-background div has a gradient from red to green.
Image Background: The image-background div has an image as its background, and the background-size: cover; property ensures the image covers the entire div.
You can experiment with different color values and background properties to achieve various effects and styles for your web pages.